Create a Calculated Insight Using Builder

Create a calculated insight without using SQL by using the builder tool in Data Cloud.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSION SETS
NEEDED
To create calculated insights:	Data Cloud Admin
In Data Cloud, go to the Calculated Insights tab, and click New.
From the Data Space dropdown, select a data space.
You can use only the data spaces that you have access to. Only the objects that are included in the data space are available to create a calculated insight.
Click Create with Builder and click Next.
Click Calculated Insight and click Next.
Click Select an Object, select the object, and then click Next.
Add the nodes by clicking + next to the object.
You must select at least one aggregate node.
Add measures and dimensions to your insight by clicking Aggregate.
You must select at least one measure.
Under Measures, click +.
Select a metric function and the field that you want to calculate, and then click Next.
Enter the metric name, and click Apply.
Under Dimensions, click +.
Select the field that you want to group by, and click Next.
Enter the dimension name, and click Apply.
To save the aggregate node, click Apply.
(Optional) Add data, such as a join, case, filter, transform, or arithmetic expression to your insight.
Click Save and Run.
Enter the calculated insight name, and click Next.
The Calculated Insight API Name field is auto-filled.
From the Schedule dropdown, select a schedule.
Select the start date and time of the schedule.
Click Enable.

You can now view your insight on the record home page.
